name: Cheese Fondue
source: http://www.aprettylifeinthesuburbs.com/fabulous-fondue-fun/
prepTime: 10 minutes
cookTime: 20 minutes
portions: 4

ingredients:
  - (1 clove) garlic
  - (1 cup) dry white wine
  - (1 lb) Gruyere and Emmentaler cheese, shredded
  - (2 tbsp) cornstarch
  - (2 tbsp) fresh lemon juice

steps:
  - Rub the inside of the fondue pot with garlic halves.
  - Pour wine into fondue pot, heat over med. low until just barely boiling.
  - Begin adding cheese by the handful, stirring until melted.
  - Mix cornstarch and lemon juice in a small bowl with a whisk until cornstarch
    dissolves.
  - Stir cornstarch mixture into cheese mixture.
  - Serve immediately with crusty bread cut into bite-size chunks, pre-cooked
    meat, and fresh or cooked vegetables.
